<TITLE> Oil falls more than $1/bbl ahead of OPEC meeting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SINGAPORE, Nov 28, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Oil fell more than $1 a barrel to below $54 on Friday, as OPEC ministers prepared to meet in Cairo on Saturday to discuss falling prices and another potential supply cut amid weakening oil demand. US light crude for January delivery fell to $53.35 a barrel by 1:48 a.m. GMT (8:48 p.m. EST), down $1.09 versus Wednesday's close. The NYMEX trading floor was closed on Thursday due to the US Thanksgiving holiday. London Brent crude was down 41 cents a barrel at $52.72, having settled 79 cents lower on Thursday
